  "articleSummary": "The article critiques common Promise anti-patterns found in popular JavaScript resources (CallbackHell.com, StrongLoop, RisingStack, and the Q library). Its core thesis is that many widely-used examples and libraries, especially Q's deferred pattern, are not true Promises and introduce unnecessary complexity. The tone is analytical and self-aware (the author admits past guilt), framed as a code review to help developers spot warning signs. The intended audience is JavaScript developers familiar with Promises, and the article is part of the \"Escape From Callback Mountain\" project.",
